This place was awesome! Everything here is super fresh. The guy who served me was understanding of all our food allergies and very accommodating. I ordered a mahi mahi taco and a chorizo taco, which were both amazing. The kid who dressed my taco said they had a special fish taco sauce and would I like to try it. He gave me a little taste on a spoon before dressing my taco with it with my approval. They let me pick all my toppings (unlimited) and when I asked for recommendations, gave me good choices! Their chorizo and Oaxacan cheese is made in house and delicious. My husband had a salad, which he wouldn't share a bite of because it was too yummy. And my kids had all eaten their food before I'd even tasted mine to write this post. To kids had burritos and two had tacos.

This place is by far my favorite restaurant near UMMC. Food is authentic, delicious, and the quantity is outstanding for the cost. Staff is always pleasant and great at getting through long lines. I tell all my friends and classmates to try it out and they all agree!

This is a really great place if you want authentic tacos de Mexico, and I think, one of the only places in Baltimore that sells both elote and nopalitos. The prices are reasonable, the portions are generous, and the menu is straightforward. They have great quality products, and you can add all the toppings you could possibly want. This is our new "go-to" taco place during the week (...and when we want burritos too!).

Legit tacos. They are on point when it comes to the topping. Awesome pico even had grilled nopales as a topping. The green salsa was very authentic and tasted great. They use purple corn tortillas here making it even more appealing to the palate.

Found this place when I was seeing Hamilton at the Hippodrome. It's perfectly placed across the street from the theater for a quick bite to eat. I absolutely love this place. I ordered the pulled pork and two chicken tacos and wish I had gotten all pulled pork because oh my God it was AMAZING. There was a wonderful burst of flavor. I was also overjoyed with the amount of toppings to choose from and when I got up to the front and they said they didn't charge for guac on the tacos. Score!!! Definitely recommend this place and I will be back.

This is the real deal! Having moved to Baltimore from California, I'm always on the lookout for good tacos in the city and this is the one to beat! The tacos and everything else on the menu are so flavorful and fresh. Plus, Jorge loves sharing his food with others and it really shows. Insider tip: ask for the traditional toppings on the tacos. Jorge has a suggested way he dresses up each one and he really knows how to make each one sing!

Omg this was absolutely delicious!!!! The guac was fresh the steak was tender and flavorful and they were not shy with their fixings. I made the mistake of getting 6 tacos when I only needed 3 but I will definitely enjoy my remaining 3 tacos for a late snack !!!
